All development was done on a Linux (Ubuntu 18.04) box. Some (or all?) of these
tools are may be available for other platforms.  Ensure that 1-4 are installed
and available in your path

(1) adb
>$ sudo apt-get install android-sdk-platform-tools

After installing add the following to /lib/udev/rules.d/51-android.rules if
there is not an entry for these venodrs/products

#Archos (Tesco Hudl - needed to allow adb to work without root permission)
SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTR{idVendor}=="0e79", ENV{adb_user}="yes"
#Rockchip RK3188(Hudl in bootloader/flash mode - needed to allow rkflashtool to work without root permission)
SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTR{idVendor}=="2207", ATTR{idProduct}=="310b", ENV{adb_user}="yes"

(2) rkflashtool & rkmisc
>$ sudo apt-get install rkflashtool

(3) imgrepackerrk
https://forum.xda-developers.com/showthread.php?t=2257331
For packing and unpacking monolithic rockchip format .img files

On 64-bit Ubuntu I needed to enable 32-bit apps with:
>$ sudo dpkg --add-architecture i386
>$ sudo apt-get install libc6-i386

(4) Tools for generating the bootanimation (see bootanimation/mkanimation:
zip & unzip: >$ sudo apt-get install zip unzip
composite:   >$ sudo apt-get install imagemagick
zopflipng:   >$ sudo apt-get install zopfli

(5) apktool
(not required, but useful for instpecting the contents of .apk files)
https://ibotpeaches.github.io/Apktool/install/
